# Session Exports Directory

This directory stores exported session logs from the Claude Code Developer Course.

## What Gets Exported

When you complete a seminar module, the course engine can export your session data:

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `seminarN-session-{uuid}.json` | Full session log with all messages and tool calls |
| `seminarN-summary-{uuid}.json` | Summary stats (duration, tool usage, errors) |
| `seminarN-report.html` | Visual HTML report (optional) |

## When Export Happens

Export is offered:
1. When you complete all tasks in a module (`/validate` passes)
2. When you explicitly request export during validation

## Manual Export

If you want to export a session manually:

```bash
# In a Claude Code session, use the cclogviewer MCP:

# List recent sessions
mcp__cclogviewer__list_sessions(project="<your-repo>", days=7)

# Export session logs
mcp__cclogviewer__get_session_logs(
  session_id="<session-uuid>",
  output_path="./exports/my-session.json"
)

# Generate HTML report
mcp__cclogviewer__generate_html(
  session_id="<session-uuid>",
  output_path="./exports/my-report.html",
  open_browser=true
)
```

## Privacy Notes

- Session logs contain your conversation with Claude
- Logs may include file paths and code snippets from your repository
- Consider this before sharing exports

## Cleaning Up

To remove old exports:

```bash
rm exports/seminar*-*.json exports/seminar*-*.html
```

Keep this `.gitkeep` file to preserve the directory in git.
